subSubSection.paragraph:
Food and Feeding.
The Papuan Mosaic-tailed Rat is presumably mycophagus: contents of nine stomachs included parts of mushrooms. Dentary and skull anatomy may relate to a special diet, shared bythe Karoko Hill Rat (
Bunomys karokophilus
), the Montane Hill Rat (
B. penitus
), and possibly the White-toothed Mouse (
Brassomys albidens
).
